<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
CONTEST TO STRESS WATER CONSERVATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ventura County is holding its first water-efficient landscaping contest to 
publicize the need for water conservation. 
</P>
<P>
The Ventura County Water Conservation Program will accept landscape entries 
that are compatible with the semiarid climate and are water-efficient, said 
Deborah Weinstock, water conservation assistant. 
</P>
<P>
The judging categories will be irrigation practice, water management, plant 
selection and culture, lawn type and size, overall water efficiency and 
landscape design and aesthetics. 
</P>
<P>
"If the whole thing is lawn, that wouldn't be considered water-efficient," 
Weinstock said. "But if there's a small portion of lawn with other plants that 
are water-efficient, that would be eligible. 
</P>
<P>
"The contest is an educational program to show that water-efficient landscapes 
can be very, very beautiful, and we'd just like to recognize those people who 
have already put them in," Weinstock said. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline is April 27. For entry forms, call 805-654-2466 or 805-654-2440. 
PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
