SUSPECT WALKS AWAY FROM HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A prisoner being treated Friday at Mercy Hospital walked away from custody, 
apparently after a private security guard unhooked the man's chains, sheriff's 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Robledo, 34, of Cerritos, who was arrested on suspicion of felony 
hit-and-run driving and evading arrest, walked out of the hospital about 2:30 
p.m. and was still missing Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Roy Stamper of the Sheriff's Department said Robledo was injured in a 
traffic accident after a high-speed chase. He was taken to the hospital and 
placed under the watch of a security guard for the Holmes Security Co. 
</P>
<P>
Stamper said the private company contracts with the county to provide hospital 
protection. The guard apparently unchained the prisoner against regulations, 
and Robledo slipped away unnoticed through a door adjoining the shower, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The escapee was described as white, 5-foot-9, 170 pounds, with blond hair and 
hazel eyes. "He was wearing hospital garb when he left," Stamper said. 
</P>
