<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN PLEADS GUILTY TO 2ND-DEGREE MURDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 30-year-old Los Angeles man pleaded guilty Friday to second-degree murder for 
strangling a Canoga Park woman during a burglary last year. 
</P>
<P>
Nicholas L. Mecca was sentenced to 16 years to life in prison for killing 
Barbara Shanks, 46, on April 17, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys Superior Court Judge Alan B. Haber sentenced Mecca to an additional 
four years in prison for burglarizing Shanks' house. 
</P>
<P>
Mecca originally was charged with first-degree murder but pleaded guilty before 
his trial to the reduced charge, said Deputy Dist. Atty. Ann Korban. 
</P>
<P>
Mecca came to Shanks' house in the 6500 block of Comanche Avenue early on the 
morning of April 17 seeking Shanks' daughter, a friend. The daughter was not 
home at the time, said Detective Michael Lewin. 
</P>
<P>
Mecca apparently became angry with Shanks and strangled her, then beat her on 
the head with several wine bottles, Korban said. The home was ransacked, but it 
was not known what, if anything, was taken, she said. 
</P>
<P>
Mecca was arrested later after he told several people about the killing, Korban 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
