LIMBAUGH'S HECKLERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your silence is deafening. . . . 
</P>
<P>
KFI-AM's infamous Rush Limbaugh appeared on "The Pat Sajak Show" March 30. 
</P>
<P>
As I write this, it is four days later. This is The Times' town. Has the 
newspaper lost its voice? 
</P>
<P>
Yes, Rick Du Brow had a short item April 3 in which he used the rather benign 
term "hecklers." But it doesn't take much imagination to visualize The Times' 
outrage had the victim been a liberal and the hecklers what the media usually 
calls "dangerous and fascistic right-wing extremist censors who are destroying 
free speech." 
</P>
<P>
ANN NORMAN, Newport Beach 
