<P>
PLAYERS HEADED FOR NFL SHOULDN'T BE HIS CONCERN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I found USC football Coach Larry Smith's concern regarding junior football 
players leaving school for jobs in the NFL interesting. May I respectfully 
suggest he need not worry about these young men, but rather he should concern 
himself with the large number of scholarship football players at USC who leave 
after their senior years, without degrees and without jobs? 
</P>
<P>
RALPH H. SPEAKMAN JR., Covina 
</P>
