<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LORRAINE GIVES ORAL COMMITMENT TO STANFORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andrew Lorraine, a senior left-hander from Hart High, said Friday he has orally 
committed to play baseball for Stanford. 
</P>
<P>
Lorraine, 4-0 with four saves, an 0.51 earned-run average and 65 strikeouts in 
41 innings, also visited Cal, USC, Loyola Marymount and Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
Stanford, which won consecutive national championships in 1987 and 1988, does 
not have a left-hander on its traveling squad, and Lorraine said he may start 
or relieve. Lorraine has a 3.75 grade-point average. 
</P>
</TEXT>
