<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR DEADHEADS, BYPASSING IRVINE WILL BE NO BIG DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So it's on to Carson . . . bye-bye, Irvine. ("Grateful Dead Tour to Bypass 
Orange County," April 3.) 
</P>
<P>
As a Grateful Dead fan, I have danced in the sunshine in Eugene, Ore., along 
the beaches in Ventura . . . and, yes, under a bright, full moon at Irvine 
Meadows. 
</P>
<P>
The settings change -- as do the seasons -- each show becoming its own unique 
slice of life. We come for the band and for each other. The venue matters 
little. 
</P>
<P>
My hat's off to the city of Irvine, shivering in the dark behind guarded gates, 
peeking warily through cracked blinds and nodding in silent approval over their 
ingenious solution to bring people together and make the world a better place 
to live. 
</P>
<P>
JEFF KAHL, Corona del Mar 
</P>
</TEXT>
