<P>
CODE EXPERT HELD AS E. GERMAN SPY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A code expert from West Germany's mission to the North Atlantic Treaty 
Organization in Brussels has been seized on suspicion of spying for East 
Germany. The case may have done enormous damage to the Western Alliance, 
officials said. The officer, whose name was not given, is being held in West 
Germany on suspicion of having passed alliance secrets to East Germany for more 
than 20 years. 
</P>
