<P>
TOURIST KILLING MAY BE TIED TO 2 OTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police say the killing earlier this week of a teen-age tourist from Michigan 
may be related to two similar slayings of young women in the same area since 
January. Police had been reluctant to comment on the growing fears about a 
serial killer stalking young women in the sprawling rows of apartment buildings 
in the neighborhood near Mission Bay. 
</P>
<P>
But police released a statement after the stabbing death Tuesday of Holly 
Suzanne Tarr, 18, a high school tourist from Okemos, Mich. Because of two 
similar cases in recent months, "We can't discount the possibility that the 
three may have been committed by the same person," police spokeswoman Dorothy 
Powell said. "All of the victims were young women. All were students. All were 
murdered in upstairs apartments. And all were stabbed during the day." 
</P>
