<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOP MATCHUPS SET FOR ARCADIA MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Arcadia Invitational track meet, with a field that includes high school 
athletes from 15 states and virtually every top prep track performer in 
California, is today at Arcadia High School. 
</P>
<P>
The open events begin at 11 a.m., and the invitational portion of the meet 
starts at 4 p.m. with the discus. 
</P>
<P>
The boys' events feature several outstanding matchups, especially in the 
middle-distance and distance races, with Coley Candaele of Carpinteria, Danny 
Jordan of Venice and Bryan Dameworth of Agoura going against some of the best 
runners in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
The girls' events will be highlighted by the 100 and 200 meters, which will 
feature three of the top sprinters in the U.S.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
