<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NAVRATILOVA AND CAPRIATI GET VICTORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three-time champion Martina Navratilova and teen-ager Jennifer Capriati took 
vastly different routes Friday to reach the semifinals of the $500,000 Family 
Circle Magazine Cup. 
</P>
<P>
Navratilova, seeded first and ranked second in the world, defeated Katerina 
Maleeva, 6-0, 6-1, in 55 minutes at Hilton Head Island, S.C. 
</P>
<P>
Capriati took more than twice as long -- and lost her first set of the 
tournament -- but beat Helen Kelesi of Canada, 6-2, 4-6, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Navratilova meets Regina Rajchrtova and Capriati faces Natalia Zvereva of the 
Soviet Union. The unseeded Rajchrtova, of Czechoslovakia, upset third-seeded 
Zina Garrison, 4-6, 6-3, 6-1. Zvereva beat Conchita Martinez of Spain, 7-6 
(8-6), 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
Capriati, 14, who had not lost more than four games in a set in her first three 
matches here, is 12-2 since turning pro last month. 
</P>
<P>
MaliVai Washington earned his first professional semifinal berth with a 6-3, 
7-5 upset of fourth-seeded Scott Davis in a $250,000 tournament at Orlando, 
Fla. 
</P>
<P>
David Pate also reached the semifinals by defeating Stanford University 
freshman Alex Hombrecher, 6-4, 7-6 (7-5). 
</P>
<P>
Washington, 20, who won three qualifying matches to gain a berth in the main 
draw, is the world's 152nd-ranked player. Last year he was the top-ranked U.S. 
college player while at Michigan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
