<HEADLINE>
<P>
AGASSI, CHESNOKOV TO PLAY TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andre Agassi will play Andrei Chesnokov of the Soviet Union in an exhibition at 
7:30 tonight at the Forum as part of the Forum Tennis Challenge. 
</P>
<P>
Agassi is ranked No. 4 after winning two tournaments this year and has three 
victories over other players in the top 10. Agassi's 16-2 record in 1990 is his 
best start. Chesnokov is ranked No. 21. 
</P>
<P>
Pepperdine teammates David Wells-Roth and Alejo Mancisidor will play in an 
earlier match. 
</P>
