<TEXT>
<P>
G-7 Ministers to Meet: Top economic policy-makers of the United States and its 
major economic allies meet today in Paris amid mounting pressures for some sort 
of new international action to calm the chaotic Japanese financial markets 
before their turmoil spreads around the globe. Japanese Finance Minister 
Ryutaro Hashimoto is expected to press finance ministers and central bankers of 
the other large industrialized countries -- known informally as the Group of 
Seven -- either to reduce their interest rates or to intervene heavily in the 
currency markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
