FIRE ALARM ABORTS FLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A USAir jet carrying 68 people made an emergency landing Friday at Logan 
International Airport after a smoke indicator light warned of a possible fire 
on board, officials said. The Boeing 737 landed safely and there were no 
injuries. No flames were found. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA040790-0131 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 201073 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
