<P>
HELP IN IDENTIFYING DEAD WOMAN ASKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities are asking public help in identifying a woman who was struck and 
killed by a car Sunday night in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was not carrying identification when she was struck near the 
intersection of Pacific Coast Highway and Newland Avenue at 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
A County Sheriff's Department spokesman said the woman was white and about 18 
years old, with brown hair, brown eyes and a slender build. 
</P>
<P>
She wore a black cotton dress, a red long-sleeve shirt, a pink sweater and had 
human hair wrapped around her left ring finger. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach Police Sgt. Carl Vidano said that the driver of the car 
involved in the accident immediately came forward and no foul play is 
suspected. 
</P>
<P>
Senior Deputy Coroner Joe Luckey is seeking information, at (714) 647-7400. 
</P>
